Class MainGLEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • graphicmotor.MainGLEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GLEventListener, EventListener

    public class MainGLEvent
extends Object
implements GLEventListener
    MainGLEvent is a basic implementation of the interface GLEventListener provide by JOGL

    It has to use an entityBank to know which entity he has to work with

      • display

        public void display(GLAutoDrawable drawable)
        see : GLEventListener.display(GLAutoDrawable).

        This method will:

        • paint the canvas in black
        • Entity may need a valid GL instance to be initialized and it's not such easy to create this kind of instance.

          So we launch the Entity.init(GL2) method to init entities who need to.

        • Iterate the entities of its EntitiesBank and call method Entity.render(GL2, GLU, GLUT) for each enabled entity
        • And finally swap the buffers
        Specified by:
        display in interface GLEventListener
